thus, inhibition of mtor can have direct effects on
tumor cells manifest by slowing proliferation, increasing
apoptosis or inhibiting tumor-derived vascular endothe-
lial growth factor (vegf), or indirect effects on tumor
cells by directly targeting the proliferation and survival
of vascular and smooth muscle stromal cells.
